rkflows** to meet 30-day deadlines.  \n\n---\n\n### 3. Data Security Measures (10% Compliance)  \n**Risk Level:** Critical  \n**Implications:** Lack of encryption/RBAC increases breach risks and non-compliance penalties.  \n\n**Action Items:**  \n1. **Encrypt/mask data** using **Informatica Cloud Data Masking**.  \n2. **Enforce RBAC/MFA** with **Informatica Cloud Data Access Management (CDAM)**.  \n3. **Monitor threats** via **Informatica’s partnership with securiti.ai** for real-time alerts.  \n\n---\n\n### 4. Data Breach Notification (16.7% Compliance)  \n**Risk Level:** High  \n**Implications:** Failure to notify within 72 hours violates DPDP Section 7(2)(b).  \n\n**Action Items:**  \n1. **Develop an escalation protocol** with automated regulatory reporting.  \n\n---\n\n### 5. Data Retention & Erasure (37.5% Compliance)  \n**Risk Level:** Medium  \n**Implications:** Manual processes delay compliance with erasure requests.  \n\n**Action Items:**  \n1. **Automate erasure** using **Informatica’s NIST 800-88-compliant tools**.  \n\n---\n\n### 6. Data Accuracy (0% Compliance)  \n**Risk Level:** High  \n**Implications:** Inaccurate data undermines compliance and decision-making.  \n\n**Action Items:**  \n1. **Adopt Informatica Cloud Data Quality** for profiling/cleansing.  \n2. **Automate audit logs** with **Informatica Log Analyzer**.  \n\n---\n\n### 7. Children’s Data Protection (33.3% Compliance)  \n**Risk Level:** Medium  \n**Implications:** Weak parental consent mechanisms risk violating DPDP Section 10.  \n\n**Action Items:**  \n1. **Integrate digital ID verification** for parental consent.  \n\n---\n\n### 8. Cross-Border Transfers (33.3% Compliance)  \n**Risk Level:** Medium  \n**Implications:** Uncontrolled transfers may breach jurisdictional requirements.  \n\n**Action Items:**  \n1. **Formalize transfer policies** with **Informatica Cloud Data Governance**.  \n\n---\n\n### 9. Documentation & Compliance (50% Compliance)  \n**Risk Level:** Medium  \n**Implications:** Incomplete documentation complicates audits.  \n\n**Action Items:**  \n1. **Appoint a DPO** and document processes via **Informatica Cloud Data Governance**.  \n\n---\n\n## Prioritized Action Plan  \n1. **Critical (Weeks 1–4):**  \n   - Deploy **Informatica Data Privacy Management** for security/rights automation.  \n   - Implement **Informatica Cloud Data Masking** for encryption.  \n2. **High (Weeks 5–8):**  \n   - Automate erasure/audit logs with **Informatica IICS**.  \n3. **Medium (Weeks 9–12):**  \n   - Formalize cross-border policies and children’s data safeguards.  \n\n---\n\n## Strategic Recommendations  \n* **Leverage Informatica’s end-to-end suite** (Governance, Privacy, Masking) for scalable compliance.  \n* **Conduct quarterly DPIAs** using **Informatica’s risk assessment tools**.  \n* **Partner with Informatica experts** to close gaps efficiently.  \n\n**Contact:** info@datainfa.com for DPDP implementation support.  \n```",
